    <stitle>NEWAY AIR SUSPENSION - SPECIFICATIONS - SPECIAL PROCESS WITH "SMART NUTS"</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl0300201" svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>SPECIAL PROCESS WITH "SMART NUTS"</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>Special "Smart Nuts" are utilized in this assembly in several locations. Smart nuts should not
                        be reused after removal and should not be replaced with other type fasteners.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Smart Nut Tightening Procedure:</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">The temperature of the nut assembly and associated parts must be 32&#176;F (0&#176;C) or
                    greater during assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">An impact wrench or hand wrench may be used to tighten the nut.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect the bolt threads and nut mating surfaces to insure that they are free of rust or
                    dirt and not damaged. Do not lubricate.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten "Smart Nut" until snug.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Continue to tighten the "smart nut" until plastic squeezes out from under the nut face
                    (about 3/4 turn) and can be removed with effort no greater than required to turn a page in a book.
                    Refer to Steps 1, 2 and 3 in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0300225">Figure 25</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0300225" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0300225" filename="../figg03/G0300225.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 25. INSTALLING "SMART NUTS"</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. STEP 1</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. STEP 2</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. STEP 3</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
